{"TopicId":164761,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Any way to change default FOV","CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-24T12:11:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-24T12:11:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello everyone!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder, is there is any way to change default Field Of View in KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSettings (I doubt), line in config, may be a mod for that?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know FOV is adjustable by alt\u002Bmouse scroll, but would be cool to have smaller FOV by default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022WzINndE.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/WzINndE.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022cB5gTeI.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/cB5gTeI.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022c3BFasu.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/c3BFasu.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pWMoUY6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/pWMoUY6.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith lesser FOV everything looks more \u0022natural\u0022 and \u0022alive\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany games have FOV slider or at least configurable FOV in files. Does KSP have it too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-24T12:27:38Z\u0022 title=\u002208/24/2017 12:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by evileye.x\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-24T14:23:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223156114\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164761\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221503576675\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022evileye.x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, evileye.x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany games have FOV slider or at least configurable FOV in files. Does KSP have it too?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot as far as I know.\u00A0 I expect it would be a pretty simple mod to write.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems like the kind of thing you\u0027d expect to find in Settings.cfg or Physics.cfg (even if it doesn\u0027t have an in-game UI), but I looked just now and didn\u0027t see anything that looked relevant.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a post over in the Suggestions forum may be in order?\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EpicSpaceTroll139","CreatedById":162839,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-30T22:21:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI seem to recall that alt\u002B and alt- change the field of view... Or something like that... Don\u0027t know about changing the default tho\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-30T22:22:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/30/2017 10:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 30, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by EpicSpaceTroll139\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}